# ICU Clinical Decision Support System — Cursor Master Prompt

Use this as the authoritative project rule. Every module built in this repository must conform to these specs unless a section explicitly says otherwise.

## 1. Project overview

Build a multi-model clinical decision support system (CDSS) for ICUs, trained on MIMIC-IV data.
The system runs five interconnected ML models and surfaces all outputs through a single plain-English bedside report.

| # | Model | Core task |
|---|-------|-----------|
| 1 | Sepsis predictor | Flag patients likely to develop sepsis 6–12 h before clinical diagnosis |
| 2 | ICU bed demand forecaster | Predict unit-level bed counts needed in the next 24–72 h |
| 3 | Ventilator forecaster | Predict which patients will need mechanical ventilation and for how long |
| 4 | Length-of-stay (LOS) estimator | Predict remaining ICU days per patient, updated every hour |
| 5 | Clinical summary generator | Translate all model outputs into plain English for the bedside clinician |

